<subSubSection id="53C46502FFD9D57AFF4255EA2C92FE60" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="520" pageId="8" pageNumber="519" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1B613689FFD9D57BFF4255EA2B61F9F4" blockId="8.[151,1437,1215,2033]" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFF4255EA2E09FB30" bold="true" box="[151,267,1215,1241]" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to the description, this species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DCDE4D0AFFD9D57BFC7B55EA2B5CFB30" authority="Pic" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1911" box="[942,1118,1215,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Anthocomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="519" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coreanus">
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFC7B55EA2B31FB31" box="[942,1075,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">A. coreanus</emphasis>
Pic
</taxonomicName>
but differs in colouration of legs and elytra. The 
<typeStatus id="C465882BFFD9D57BFE5555B62EE0FB14" box="[384,482,1251,1277]" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">holotype</typeStatus>
was described with no indication of sex, but since the elytral apices are simple and lack impressions or appendages, it should be transferred from 
<taxonomicName id="DCDE4D0AFFD9D57BFC8054522B49FAC8" authority="Erichson" authorityName="Erichson. This" authorityYear="1840" box="[853,1099,1287,1313]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Anthocomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="519" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFC8054522CDDFAC8" box="[853,991,1287,1313]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">Anthocomus</emphasis>
Erichson
</taxonomicName>
if the 
<typeStatus id="C465882BFFD9D57BFB4154522BF4FAC8" box="[1172,1270,1287,1313]" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">holotype</typeStatus>
is a male. The main differential characters from the original description are as follows: elytra and pronotum black with yellow lateral edges, elytral apices simple, lacking impressions or appendages, with red markings near suture; antennae long and strong, with elongate wide triangular intermediate antennomeres, anterior and intermediate legs yellow, except for darkened tarsi, posterior legs black with yellow coxae and trochanters; palpi yellow with darkened apices. The colour of upperside similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="DCDE4D0AFFD9D57BFD3754EE2C9EFA3C" authority="Pic" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1911" box="[738,924,1467,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Anthocomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="519" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coreanus">
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFD3754EE2C69FA3D" box="[738,875,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">A. coreanus</emphasis>
Pic
</taxonomicName>
, which is comparable with 
<taxonomicName id="DCDE4D0AFFD9D57BFB3654EE2DA7FA10" authority="Wittmer, 1984" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1984" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Haplomalachius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="519" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forticornis" subGenus="Flabellomalachius">
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFB3654EE2A9EFA3C" box="[1251,1436,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">Haplomalachius</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFF74548A2E71FA10" box="[161,371,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">Flabellomalachius</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFE51548A2EF8FA10" box="[388,506,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">forticornis</emphasis>
Wittmer, 1984
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DCDE4D0AFFD9D57BFD0B548A2FCDF9F4" authority="Sato, Wittmer, 1989" authorityName="Sato, Wittmer" authorityYear="1989" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Haplomalachius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="519" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ishiharai" subGenus="Flabellomalachius">
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFD0B548A2C95FA10" box="[734,919,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">Haplomalachius</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFC7D548A2B78FA10" box="[936,1146,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">Flabellomalachius</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFB59548A2BF3FA10" box="[1164,1265,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">ishiharai</emphasis>
Satô, Wittmer, 1989
</taxonomicName>
and the locally distributed 
<taxonomicName id="DCDE4D0AFFD9D57BFDD457562DB8F9F4" authorityName="Sato, Wittmer" authorityYear="1989" box="[513,698,1539,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Haplomalachius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ishiharai" subGenus="Flabellomalachius">
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFDD457562D1EF9F5" box="[513,540,1539,1564]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFDF957562D3FF9F5" box="[556,573,1539,1564]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">F</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFD8057562DB8F9F4" box="[597,698,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">ishiharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subspecies 
<emphasis id="29AAEA9BFFD9D57BFC9557562CB7F9F4" box="[832,949,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">kasantsevi</emphasis>
Wittmer, 1996.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B613689FFD9D57AFF1257722DC5FF3C" blockId="8.[151,1437,1215,2033]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1437,151,467]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="520" pageId="8" pageNumber="519">
The original text of the description in 
